definition.value: Trypanosoma cruzi seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating T. cruzi specific antibodies

Quantification of the fraction of nitric oxide in the total exhalation volume, used as a non-invasive biomarker of eosinophilic airway inflammation. Higher Feno values are associated with childhood asthma symptoms, exacerbations, physician-diagnosed asthma and atopy.
quantification of the capacity of a given individual to generate thrombin, measured in plasma and shown to associate with thrombotic disorders
The age at which an alcohol diagnosis was made in a human patient
The age at which a breast cancer diagnosis was made in a human patient
A measure of cortical opacity used in the diagnosis of cataract.
This line was haploid when it was established. Like other lines, it may go back in forth in ploidy (by factors of two), depending on the growth conditions and the general health of the cells.
Cells are from the ventral leg imaginal disc of the third instar larval stage. Transcriptome analysis suggests similarity to cells in the tibia or femur region of a leg disc (Cherbas et al., 2011).
quantification of some metabolite in serum
quantification of the speed at which sound travels through bone as an indicator of the physical and structural properties of the bone
Is the quantification of Beta-amyloid 1-40 in plasma, typically used as a biomarker for Alzheimer's Disease
Is the quantification of Beta-amyloid 1-42 in plasma, typically used as a biomarker for Alzheimer's Disease
The CBCL is a widely used checklist of between 100 and 120 questions (depending on target age group) for identifying problem behaviour in children.
quantification of the glycoprotein uromodulin in urine
quantification of some metabolite in blood
quantification of white matter hyperintensity, usually measured by MRI
quantification of the antibodies to the enzyme thyroid peroxidase in blood, usually as an indicator for autoimmune thyroid disease
quantification of the amount of albumin excreted in urine, measured as an indicator for kidney malfunctions such as diabetic nephropathy
quantification of the depth of the anterior chamber of the eye as an indicator for eye disease such as primary angle closure glaucoma
the quantification of some smoking or smoking-related behaviour, usually self-reported via a questionnaire
quantification of the microstructre of the white matter of the brain
the quantification of vitamin D-binding protein in blood as a biomarker for vitamin D-related diseases such as osteoporosis, arthritis, cardiovascular disease and cancer

quantification of the onset of puberty in human males and females through a series of proxy measurements such as genital enlargement (males) or breast development (females). These characteristics are assessed based on pre-defined scales either through self-reporting or through assessment by a medical professional.
The determination of the amount of omega-6 polyunsaturated fatty acids present in a sample.
quantification of the relative amount of oxygen that is dissolved or carried in a given medium

The quantification of NHDL cholesterol in blood, calculated by subtracting the amount of cholesterol in the HDL fraction from total cholesterol and used as an indicator for cardiovascular disease risk
The quantification in blood of trimethylamine N-oxide, a product of gut microbiome and hepatic-mediated metabolism of dietary choline and L-carnitine

KMS-11 cell line was derived from four patients with multiple myeloma. These cells represent a later stage of B-cell differentiation, and shows characteristics of plasma cells by secreting surface kappa chain immunoglobulins.
Medulloblastoma (aka D721), surgical resection from a patient with medulloblastoma as described by Darrell Bigner (1997)

M059J cells were isolated from a tumor specimen taken from a 33 year old male with untreated malignant glioblastoma. The cells were isolated concurrently from the same tumor specimen as M059K (see CRL-2365).

The Daoy cell line was established in 1985 by P. F Jacobsen of the Royal Perth Hospital in Western Australia. The line was derived from biopsy material taken from a tumor in the posterior fossa of a 4 year old boy.

This is an adherent cell line derived from a hepatic rhabdoid tumor. Hepatic rhabdoid tumors are extremely rare. This cell line has a large deletion on 22q, which indicates numerous genes in addition to SNF5 are deleted.
A malignant rhabdoid tumor diploid cell population cloned from the A204 ATCC cell line. [PMID: 16897758]

This is an adherent cell line that represents the prototypical renal rhabdoid tumor [PMID: 16897758]. G401.6 is a diploid, 6-thioguanine-resistant clonal variant of the G401 cell line isolated by Weissman et al., Science, 236:175-180 (1986). The parental cell line, G401, can be ordered from the ATCC (CRL1441).

HuH-7 is a well differentiated hepatocyte derived cellular carcinoma cell line that was originally taken from a liver tumor in a 57-year-old Japanese male in 1982. The line was established by Nakabayshi, H. and Sato, J. HuH-7 is an immortal cell line of epithelial-like tumorigenic cells. It usually grow in 2D monolayers. HuH7.5 developed from HuH7.

Nasal biopsies were collected from volunteer donors as an outpatient procedure as described (Feron et al., 1998). This was done by a registered otolaryngologist via an endoscopic procedure to ensure biopsy samples were taken from the superior, posterior region of the nasal septum close to the cribriform plate. Pieces of olfactory mucosa were obtained which contain stem cells in the olfactory epithelium. The stem cell population derived from human olfactory mucosa has been described as ecto-mesenchymal (Delorme et al., 2010) because it has characteristics of both neural and mesenchymal stem cells, suggesting a neural crest origin.

in the Surgery Branch of the NCI.">This cell line was from a melanoma metastasis tumor taken from the subcutaneous shoulder of an individual. Cell line was derived by Dr. Yardena Samuels (samuelsy[at]mail.nih.gov)

This line was derived from a primary clear cell adenocarcinoma. The karyotype is hypertriploid; Y was present in 60% the cells examined. The cells display both microvilli and desmosomes, and can be grown in soft agar. The cells produce a PTH like peptides that is identical to peptides produced by breast and lung tumors.

First trimester human trophoblast cells established by immortalizing a physiologic extravillous trophoblast cell via transfection with a plasmid containing the simian virus 40 large T antigen (SV40) (see Graham et al., 1993). Cells are a thin layer of ectoderm that forms the wall of many mammalian blastulas and functions in the nutrition and implantation of the embryo.

This is an adherent cell line. HFF-Myc are human foreskin fibroblasts containing a virally integrated vector expressing the canine cMyc gene. Cells were received from Dr. Beverly Torok-Storb, Fred Hutchison Cancer Research Center, Seattle, WA.

Normal benign adult human pancreatic duct cells immortalized with E6E7 gene of HPV-16. HPDE6-E6E7 cells demonstrated a near normal genotype and phenotype of pancreatic duct epithelial cells. [PMC1861644]

Human skin malignant melanoma cells that can be ordered from ATCC. This is a hyperdiploid human cell line with the modal chromosome number of 49, occurring in 24% of cells. Polyploid cells occurred at 22%, which is high. Cells are adherent, and were first harvested in 1971 from a metastatic site in a lymph node.
Human pancreas adenocarcinoma (PA-TU-8988T), "established in 1985 from the liver metastasis of a primary pancreatic adenocarcinoma from a 64-year-old woman; sister cell line of PA-TU-8988S" - DSMZ.

Skeletal myoblasts derived from satellite cells from the pectoralis major muscle of a 41 year old caucasian heart transplant donor, immortalized with lox-hygro-hTERT (LH), and Cdk4-neo (CN), Zhu et al. (2007) in Aging Cell, vol. 6, pp 515-523. M2 is an extremely well-differentiating subclone of LHCN (thus "LHCN-M2").

The WERI-Rb-1 line is one of two human retinoblastoma cell lines established in 1974 by R.M. McFall and T.W. Sery. This is a near diploid line. The modal chromosome number is 47 occurring at 38%, and the rate of polyploidy is 9%. Cells are grape-like clusters of round cells in suspension.

"The cell line Ishikawa was established from an endometrial adenocarcinoma of a 39 year old woman. Cells can be commercially obtained from Sigma (99040201-1VL). However, it should be noted that the original source of these cells (M. Nashide, Japan) can spontaneously lose the progesterone and
estrogen receptor. For details, see Nishida M., The Ishikawa cells from birth to the
present. Hum Cell. 2002 Sep;15(3):104-17."

Established from a pleural effusion of 73 year-old woman diagnosed with B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma (intra-abdominal, diffuse large cell lymphoma, refractory, terminal). Cells are available from Dr Abraham Karpas, Department of Haematology, University of Cambridge, and are round and polygonal, growing in suspension. [PMID: 2297573]

This melanoma cell line was derived from a metastatic axillary node of the skin of a 24 year old female. It is a hyperpentaploid human cell line with the modal chromosome number of 120, occurring in 9% of cells. [PMID: 1067619]
SK-N-DZ is a neuroblastoma cell line derived in 1978 from a bone marrow metastasis from a child with poorly differentiated embryonal neuroblastoma.

The line was established from cells from the bone marrow of a child with rhabdomyosarcoma. Derived from a metastatic site of the bone marrow. The cells show ultrastructural elements of primitive skeletal muscle differentiation.
